00:26:12.230 --> 00:26:13.195
They had no idea.

00:26:13.195 --> 00:26:15.320
So on the chance that they
could dig their way out,

00:26:15.320 --> 00:26:16.910
they started digging.

00:26:16.910 --> 00:26:21.390
And I mean, this is a very
very traumatized group of men.

00:26:21.390 --> 00:26:25.289
And the people that
came to the fore

00:26:25.289 --> 00:26:27.080
weren't necessarily
crew bosses or anything

00:26:27.080 --> 00:26:30.050
in an official role
as leaders, but they

00:26:30.050 --> 00:26:33.220
were very aggressive
men who grabbed

00:26:33.220 --> 00:26:36.650
a pick ax, grabbed a shovel,
started shouting orders--

00:26:36.650 --> 00:26:38.750
dig here, we're going to do--

00:26:38.750 --> 00:26:40.250
they didn't care
how people felt.

00:26:40.250 --> 00:26:42.560
Some guys were scared,
some guys were hurt--

00:26:42.560 --> 00:26:44.270
they didn't care.

00:26:44.270 --> 00:26:46.780
We've got to dig now.

00:26:46.780 --> 00:26:48.250
It didn't work.

00:26:48.250 --> 00:26:50.530
They could not
dig their way out.

00:26:50.530 --> 00:26:53.860
And they ran out of water
and they ran out of food

00:26:53.860 --> 00:26:55.660
and then they ran out of light.

00:26:55.660 --> 00:26:58.540
And eventually, they're just
sitting there in the darkness

00:26:58.540 --> 00:27:01.720
and maybe facing the prospect
that for the rest of eternity,

00:27:01.720 --> 00:27:04.810
they'd be buried two miles
down in the earth never

00:27:04.810 --> 00:27:09.240
to be dug up even as corpses.

00:27:09.240 --> 00:27:11.610
And so of course,
now the struggle

00:27:11.610 --> 00:27:14.190
becomes not physical,
but psychological.

00:27:14.190 --> 00:27:18.600
And what they needed was a
different type of leader.

00:27:18.600 --> 00:27:23.070
They needed a leader who
actually was not aggressive,

00:27:23.070 --> 00:27:25.170
who was not a go-getter.

00:27:25.170 --> 00:27:27.086
They needed someone
who was empathic,

00:27:27.086 --> 00:27:29.460
who was able to sort of take
the temperature of the group

00:27:29.460 --> 00:27:32.550
to see who was suffering so
much that they might trigger

00:27:32.550 --> 00:27:39.120
a panic in the whole group, who
needed help, who didn't, who

00:27:39.120 --> 00:27:42.300
could go without their
sip of water that day,

00:27:42.300 --> 00:27:44.876
who needed that
extra sip to get by.

00:27:44.876 --> 00:27:46.500
So there were people
that really needed

00:27:46.500 --> 00:27:49.530
these sort of communicative
skills, these empathic skills

00:27:49.530 --> 00:27:51.750
who was focused on the
unity of the group,

00:27:51.750 --> 00:27:54.150
rather than on following orders.

00:27:54.150 --> 00:27:57.690
So what psychologists who
studied these people when

00:27:57.690 --> 00:28:01.024
they eventually got them out--

00:28:01.024 --> 00:28:02.690
and they had to make
terrible decisions.

00:28:02.690 --> 00:28:06.660
One guy was pinned, his arm
was crushed between two timbers

00:28:06.660 --> 00:28:07.644
and he couldn't move.

00:28:07.644 --> 00:28:09.060
And they were
trying to figure out

00:28:09.060 --> 00:28:12.420
whether to take one of the
carpentry saws or an ax

00:28:12.420 --> 00:28:14.010
and cut him free.

00:28:14.010 --> 00:28:15.870
I mean, there were
decisions like that that

00:28:15.870 --> 00:28:17.700
had to be made in the darkness.

00:28:17.700 --> 00:28:18.930
Imagine.

00:28:18.930 --> 00:28:23.200
So what the
psychologists found was

00:28:23.200 --> 00:28:27.120
that the first kind of leader,
the really aggressive kind that

00:28:27.120 --> 00:28:28.930
didn't care how
anyone felt, that

00:28:28.930 --> 00:28:32.260
was a very classically
sort of male role.

00:28:32.260 --> 00:28:36.400
It was a very kind of
male form of leadership.

00:28:36.400 --> 00:28:40.180
But you needed more
than that in a society

00:28:40.180 --> 00:28:42.880
that has to deal with a lot
of different, some of them

00:28:42.880 --> 00:28:44.410
being emotional challenges.

00:28:44.410 --> 00:28:46.420
You can't just go with that guy.

00:28:46.420 --> 00:28:50.010
