00:41:18.040 --> 00:41:22.120
But that means that we sort of
disagree with the other side

00:41:22.120 --> 00:41:24.660
but respect that it has
its own coherent ethos

00:41:24.660 --> 00:41:27.169
and that the other side
actually thinks that way

00:41:27.169 --> 00:41:28.960
because the other side
thinks that's what's

00:41:28.960 --> 00:41:31.450
best for the country.

00:41:31.450 --> 00:41:33.529
The idea that the other
side thinks that way

00:41:33.529 --> 00:41:35.320
because it's trying to
destroy the country,

00:41:35.320 --> 00:41:37.510
that idea is completely toxic.

00:41:37.510 --> 00:41:40.720
It would never be that kind
of contempt for someone

00:41:40.720 --> 00:41:42.070
you disagree with.

00:41:42.070 --> 00:41:43.830
Disagreement's fine,
argument's fine.

00:41:43.830 --> 00:41:49.080
It makes for sort of
strong solutions, I think.

00:41:49.080 --> 00:41:52.440
But contempt for someone you
share a combat outpost with

00:41:52.440 --> 00:41:54.040
doesn't last very long.

00:41:54.040 --> 00:41:56.940
I mean, down in
Restrepo, there were

00:41:56.940 --> 00:41:59.410
guys who really
disliked each other

00:41:59.410 --> 00:42:01.210
but no one had contempt
for anyone else.

00:42:01.210 --> 00:42:03.210
You don't want to have
contempt for someone whom

00:42:03.210 --> 00:42:05.700
you may be counting
on to put a tourniquet

00:42:05.700 --> 00:42:08.400
on your femoral artery bleed.

00:42:08.400 --> 00:42:10.530
And that's what we're
doing in this country.

00:42:10.530 --> 00:42:12.321
We have contempt for
people we may actually

00:42:12.321 --> 00:42:14.280
depend on for our lives.

00:42:14.280 --> 00:42:16.800
I mean, we don't know
if or when this country

00:42:16.800 --> 00:42:18.837
will be turned into one
huge combat outpost.

00:42:18.837 --> 00:42:20.670
We have no idea when
that's going to happen.

00:42:20.670 --> 00:42:23.710
It happened in Houston
and everyone acted well.

00:42:23.710 --> 00:42:26.170
But we're really gambling
with this country

00:42:26.170 --> 00:42:28.979
of sort of institutionalizing
this partisan rhetoric

00:42:28.979 --> 00:42:31.270
where we actually have a kind
of deep loathing for half

00:42:31.270 --> 00:42:32.080
the country.

00:42:32.080 --> 00:42:33.790
Are you insane?

00:42:33.790 --> 00:42:35.580
It doesn't work.

00:42:35.580 --> 00:42:36.246
SPEAKER 1: Yeah.

00:42:40.080 --> 00:42:42.080
You mentioned moral
courage and then

00:42:42.080 --> 00:42:45.020
there was another courage,
which was more of like saving

00:42:45.020 --> 00:42:46.460
someone [INAUDIBLE] or whatnot.

00:42:46.460 --> 00:42:47.418
SEBASTIAN JUNGER: Yeah.

00:42:47.418 --> 00:42:49.610
So from studies of
sort of bystander

00:42:49.610 --> 00:42:52.100
rescues from fires
and other catastrophes

00:42:52.100 --> 00:42:53.780
that happen sort
of spontaneously

00:42:53.780 --> 00:42:57.290
in the world, what they
know from the statistics

00:42:57.290 --> 00:43:02.720
of these incidents is
that the vast majority--

00:43:02.720 --> 00:43:05.620
98% or something like that--

00:43:05.620 --> 00:43:10.210
of bystanders who spontaneously
expose themselves to danger

00:43:10.210 --> 00:43:13.090
to rescue people they don't know
who are in a burning building

00:43:13.090 --> 00:43:17.880
or whatever, almost 100%
of the people that do that

00:43:17.880 --> 00:43:20.820
are male, particularly
young male.

00:43:20.820 --> 00:43:24.420
And they will risk their lives
particularly for children--

00:43:24.420 --> 00:43:30.680
in this order, for children,
for young women, for old people,

00:43:30.680 --> 00:43:34.730
and eventually for young men.

00:43:34.730 --> 00:43:38.650
Young men are the first to
rescue and the last to get

00:43:38.650 --> 00:43:40.060
rescued, as they should be.

00:43:40.060 --> 00:43:44.170
Young men in genetic terms are
very replaceable in society,

00:43:44.170 --> 00:43:45.690
young women are not.

00:43:45.690 --> 00:43:48.907
I mean, the constraint on
the health of a society

00:43:48.907 --> 00:43:50.740
is the number of young
women, not the number

00:43:50.740 --> 00:43:53.140
of young men, which
is one of the reasons

00:43:53.140 --> 00:43:56.270
that young men are sent into
the meat grinder of World War

00:43:56.270 --> 00:44:00.710
I. If the troops in World
War I had been young women,

00:44:00.710 --> 00:44:02.710
Europe wouldn't exist anymore.

00:44:02.710 --> 00:44:04.030
It would be over.

00:44:04.030 --> 00:44:07.690
Europe recovered quite
quickly from World War I

00:44:07.690 --> 00:44:09.820
because it was almost
exclusively young males that

00:44:09.820 --> 00:44:10.730
were getting killed.

00:44:10.730 --> 00:44:12.520
Had it been millions
of young women,

00:44:12.520 --> 00:44:15.460
we would still be seeing
the consequences of that

00:44:15.460 --> 00:44:17.060
in the demographics over there.

00:44:17.060 --> 00:44:18.910
So those are the statistics.

00:44:18.910 --> 00:44:20.890
Like it or not, those
are the statistics.

00:44:20.890 --> 00:44:26.989
People using their free will
walking down the street,

00:44:26.989 --> 00:44:29.280
whether they risk their lives
to save somewhere or not,

00:44:29.280 --> 00:44:32.270
it's almost 100% male.

00:44:32.270 --> 00:44:35.510
That doesn't mean that men
are braver than women--

00:44:35.510 --> 00:44:38.660
it doesn't mean that at all.

00:44:38.660 --> 00:44:40.440
There are different
kinds of courage.

00:44:40.440 --> 00:44:43.520
And there's also moral
courage that does not depend

00:44:43.520 --> 00:44:46.520
on sort of a physical reaction.

00:44:46.520 --> 00:44:51.200
So men are adapted to that
kind of physical feat.

00:44:51.200 --> 00:44:55.100
On average, we're 20%
larger and stronger

00:44:55.100 --> 00:44:57.000
than women are on average.

00:44:57.000 --> 00:44:59.300
But there are moral
decisions that don't

00:44:59.300 --> 00:45:01.340
depend on physical strength.

00:45:01.340 --> 00:45:05.300
So during World War II,
a very serious decision

00:45:05.300 --> 00:45:10.640
that families had to make
was the Germans are coming,

00:45:10.640 --> 00:45:12.590
here's this Jewish family
we don't even know.

00:45:12.590 --> 00:45:15.010
They just showed
up in our driveway.

00:45:15.010 --> 00:45:17.210
Are we going to hide
them in the basement?

00:45:17.210 --> 00:45:21.710
We're Gentiles, we don't have
a problem with the Nazis.

00:45:21.710 --> 00:45:23.130
We're fine.

00:45:23.130 --> 00:45:26.120
But here's this Jewish family,
they're fleeing the Germans.

00:45:26.120 --> 00:45:28.250
Do we hide them or not?

00:45:28.250 --> 00:45:30.690
If we hide them,
they may survive.

00:45:30.690 --> 00:45:33.020
We don't know them, we
don't owe them anything,

00:45:33.020 --> 00:45:34.430
they just showed up.

00:45:34.430 --> 00:45:36.710
If we hide them,
they may survive.

00:45:36.710 --> 00:45:41.030
If we hide them and the
Germans discover that,

00:45:41.030 --> 00:45:43.720
everybody's dead.

00:45:43.720 --> 00:45:49.130
So women were significantly
more likely to make

00:45:49.130 --> 00:45:53.300
that morally courageous choice
of hiding a family of people

00:45:53.300 --> 00:45:56.730
they don't know who would
be killed by the Nazis,

00:45:56.730 --> 00:45:58.970
more likely them men were.

00:45:58.970 --> 00:46:03.920
It didn't require scaling
a burning building,

00:46:03.920 --> 00:46:07.040
jumping onto the railroad tracks
to help someone with a train.

00:46:07.040 --> 00:46:08.780
It didn't require
a physical act.

00:46:08.780 --> 00:46:13.890
Men, frankly, are more adapted
to that kind of physical act.

00:46:13.890 --> 00:46:15.780
But it required
incredible courage,

00:46:15.780 --> 00:46:17.115
and that's moral courage.

00:46:17.115 --> 00:46:19.470
And it's equally
important and you

00:46:19.470 --> 00:46:23.520
can't have a humane
and civil society

00:46:23.520 --> 00:46:25.920
if people are not willing
to act with moral courage.

00:46:25.920 --> 00:46:29.710
And moral courage doesn't just
mean sacrificing your life.

00:46:29.710 --> 00:46:31.210
It may mean sacrificing
your career.

00:46:31.210 --> 00:46:34.080
It actually may mean standing
on principle and saying,

00:46:34.080 --> 00:46:36.240
I cannot abide this,
I'm stepping down.

00:46:36.240 --> 00:46:39.660
I'm not running for Senate
next year or whatever.

00:46:39.660 --> 00:46:41.970
There's principles
that I have that I

00:46:41.970 --> 00:46:45.289
value more than my career
more than my party,

00:46:45.289 --> 00:46:46.080
more than anything.

00:46:46.080 --> 00:46:52.650
And as Martin Luther said, here
I stand for I can do no other.

00:46:52.650 --> 00:46:53.610
That's moral courage.

00:46:53.610 --> 00:46:57.200
It doesn't have to
be life and death.

00:46:57.200 --> 00:46:59.480
